item.title: Salmon Pokebowl
item.description: Poke bowl servings: 2 cook time: 25 minutes Ingredients: cucumbers kewpie mayo 3 tbsp mini cucumbers 2 pepper rice vinegar 1 tsp salmon 1/4-1/2 pound salt scallions seaweed sesame seeds siracha 1 tbsp soy sauce 1 tbsp sushi rice 2 cups garlic chili sauce 2 cups Cookware: Rice cooker Pan Chopsticks Steps: Start cooking sushi rice in rice cooker sushi rice: 2 cups Cut mini cucumbers into thin slices, put into bowl and splash with rice vinegar, siracha, soy sauce.

item.title: Zaxbys Kickn' Chicken
item.description: Kickin’ Chicken Servings: 1 Cook Time: 20 minutes Ingredients High Temp oil Enough to cover pan Chicken 1 Breast (Cut thin) Ranch To taste Buffalo Sauce To taste Flour 1 Cup Bread 2 Slices Steps Coat chicken breast in flour Preheat oven to 400 Put enough oil in pan to mostly cover chicken breast Slowly place chicken in oil Cook on each side for 3 minutes or until golden and crispy Place in oven until chicken is fully cooked through.
